# {project_name}

Custom QuinkGL peer generated from the `{template}` template.

## Running the Peer

```bash
python peer_main.py --swarm-id {swarm_id_short}
```

The canonical Mode C entry point (`peer_main.py`) loads the manifest,
constructs a `GossipNode`, and runs the training loop.

## Testing

```bash
pytest
```

Tests verify that `build_model` and `build_loaders` raise `NotImplementedError`
(as expected for a custom template) and that the local swarm fixture works.

